fields.descriptive_line: Series of colour prints, from Gay Way Nursery Rhyme Pictures, edited by E R Boyce, published by Macmillan & Co. Ltd. in England, c 1950
fields.physical_description:
Each sheet features a full-colour print with a plain border, with the title printed at the bottom. The brightly coloured illustrations depict a single scene from each nursery rhyme, drawn in a cartoon-like, linear style, painted with bright primary colours. 
[Humpty Dumpty] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts Humpty Dumpty, wearing a colourful jester-style outfit, sitting on a wall. In the background, a cavalry unit troupe down the hill, towards a large castle. 
[Hot Cross Buns] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts three children and their dog, in a lane, with a man in bakers' outfit selling hot cross buns.
[Hickory Dickory Dock] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts three children in a living room, with their toys around them, looking up at a mouse climbing over the clock. 
[Little Jack Horner] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a blonde boy sitting on a red table, in the corner of a room. The calendar on the wall says 'Dec 25', and a book of carols lies open in the foreground. A white cat sits near his feet.
[Polly Put the Kettle On] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts two children sitting on an upholstered bench, watching an older girl, in a white apron, holding a large metal kettle over a stove. In the foreground, a table is laid with bread, cups and saucers, and iced buns.
[This little pig went to market] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a girl in blue checked dress, sitting in a yellow rocking chair, playing with the toes of the blonde baby on her lap. Five vignettes of pigs acting out the rhyme are arranged in an arc over their heads.
[Jack Spratt] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a man and woman eating at at a table. The woman, on the left, is rotund and has a plate of white fat. Jack, wearing a blue frock coat and checked trousers, is thin and angular.
[Little Boy Blue] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a boy sleeping peacefully next to a haystack in the sunshine. An angry looking girl is trying to wake him. 
[Simple Simon] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a boy in patched clothing with blonde hair, meeting a man with a tray of pies on a country lane. There is a brightly coloured fairground in the background. The characters wear clothes of a medieval style.
[Hey Diddle Diddle] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts anthropomorphic bowl and spoon running along a lane, followed by a cat playing a fiddle and a smiling dog. Above the green hilly countryside, a large cow jumps through a crescent moon. 
[The Queen of Hearts] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a woman with a jewelled gold crown, wearing a yellow crinoline dress with red heart pattern. She is bending over a large wooden table, rolling out pastry. There is a boy in a page's uniform hiding under the table.
[There was a crooked man] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a man with bent legs and a crooked stick inside the hallway of his house, pointing to an angular cat and mouse. The furniture and fittings are all wonky and irregularly shaped. 
[Little Bo Peep] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a girl in a pink and blue dress, with black net gloves, looking into the distance. She is crying and her shepherd's crook is on the ground next to her. 
[Little Tommy Tucker] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a dark-haired boy standing in front of a laid table, with a book of sheet music. His mouth is open as if singing, to a dog who sites with ears pricked in front of an empty plate.
[I had a little nut tree] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a girl in regal dress, with a black servant holding a fan. A boy in medieval style clothes bows at their approach. The scene takes place by a tree which has gold and silver fruit. 
[Pat-a-cake, pat-a-cake, baker’s man] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a girl and boy in a bakery, excitingly contemplating a cake held aloft by a baker in white apron and hat.
[To market, to market, to buy a fat pig] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a boy with pink cheeks and pink tights, running along a lane. He is using a stick to drive a leashed pig. A sign post shows home in one direction, and market in the other. 
[Higgledy Piggledy, my black hen] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a girl in blue polka dot dress and white mob cap, collecting eggs from a chicken coop. She holds a basket which is already full. A clutch of chicks and a number of chicken peck around on the ground by her feet. 
[Ring-a-ring-a-roses] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a group of six children, who are dancing in a circle holding hands. One has fallen over onto the grass. The scene is set in a field in the countryside. 
[Pussy-cat, pussy-cat, where have you been] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a grey cat chasing a mouse under the queen's white chair. The queen has a red velvet and jewelled brown, and a blue dress with a pattern of red flowers. Two children, on the right hand of the image, are dressed in complimentary colours and style. They point, alarmed, at the cat.
[Ride a cock-horse to Banbury cross] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a finely dressed woman riding a decorated white pony down a lane. Two children, one with a hobby-horse, wave as she goes by. The woman and horse are both decked with tassles, bells, and feathers. A signpost reads 'To Banbury Cross'
[Do you know the muffin man?] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts an urban scene. Two children, one with a hoop, approach a man carrying a tray of English muffins on his head. He is wearing patched checked trousers and is ringing a bell. 
[Please to remember the fifth of November] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a boy in jacket, scarf and gloves, pushing a stuffed guy in a brightly painted wheelbarrow. Other children in the street and at the window of a nearby house look on, intrigued.
[Ding Dong bell, pussy’s in the well] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a stone well next to a house, and a group of children gathered round. A young boy is taking a wet kitten out of the well's bucket. Three other boys and two girls are all looking on, with expressions of fear, concern and anger.
[Here we go round the Mulberry bush] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a group of children, wearing winter clothes, skipping around an old, dense bush with dark foliage. The scene is set at the end of a lane, with a house or school building in the background.
[I had a little pony] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a woman, with a determined expression, whipping a dappled grey horse as it canters down a lane. A goose jumps out of teh way, and a boy and man in a nearby field look shocked at the scene.
[Three little mice sat down to spin] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts three mice sitting at spinning wheels in a cosy cottage, with a fashion plate and dressmaking designs on the wall next to finished garments. A cat in a bonnet is looking through the doorway.
[The man in the moon] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a man in checked short trousers, and a cape decorated with stars, falling through the air over a busy village. People in the street and in the windows watch his descent with a mixture of alarm and excitement.
[A farmer went trotting upon his red mare] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a large grey horse, with two riders. The farmer at the front has his feet firmly in the stirrups and confidently holds a whip. Behind him sits a young woman in a summer dress, holding a basket and looking back over her shoulder with concern, at a black raven in the tree. Two pink pigs scurry down the path. 
[Oranges and lemons] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a group of children in a urban garden. A girl and boy are making an arch with their arms, which other children are passing through. The spires of several churches are visible in the background.
[Monday’s child is fair of face] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts seven children in various poses and attitudes, in a village lane. Each has a letter somewhere on their clothing to indicate which day of the week they represent. 
[There was an old woman tossed up in a basket] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a woman in many layers of patterned clothing, sitting in basket holding a broom. She is flying upwards through the air, towards a smiling moon, over the head of a flock of lambs. A young shepherd boy calls out to her. 
[Three little kittens they lost their mittens] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts three kittens, wearing dresses and mittens, holding out their hands. They approach their mother, who sits at a table in front of a large pie, holding a knife and fork.
[I saw a ship a-sailing] Colour print on off-white paper, with plain border and title underneath. Depicts a colourful galleon with four sails, riding high in a choppy sea. The boat is populated with many mice, acting as crew and getting up to mischief. The captain is a duck wearing a bicorne hat.

fields.public_access_description:
This series of Nursery Rhyme Pictures was produced by Macmillan & Co. to support the Gay Way reading scheme. They were displayed in Winsor School, East Ham, in the 1960s. 
The series was edited by Ella Ruth Boyce, a prolific writer for children and long-term collaborator with the educational publishers.
fields.history_note:
These prints were used at Winsor School, East Ham. The series was designed to support the Gay Way reading course for primary school children. This long-standing course of handbooks, reading books and posters offered a developmental approach to reading and gradually introduced new vocabulary to the young reader.
The donor was a teacher at this school in the mid-1980s, by which  time the posters had been put in storage and considered 'far too dated'.
